            <div class="view view-our-teams view-id-our_teams view-display-id-page_1 view-dom-id-edd054f307fa32cba9059134c6d76364">
                <div class="view-header">
                    <div class="wrap">
                        <h1>Board of Directors</h1>      </div>
                </div>



                <div class="view-content">
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/3-geode-lionel-harris-heaadshot.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Lionel T. Harris, CFA</h2>
                            <h3 class="title">Chairman of the Board</h3>
                            <p>Lionel Harris has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2021. Mr.Harris has been a Strategic Advisor to Fidelity Investments’ Human Resources Enterprise Group, focusing on employee diversity and engagement, since July 2018. Fidelity Investments is a leading provider of investment management, retirement planning, portfolio guidance, brokerage, benefits outsourcing and other financial products and services to more than 30 million individuals, institutions and financial intermediaries. Since July 2018, Mr. Harris has also served on the board of Southeastern Grocers, a Florida-based food retailer.  During the preceding 13 years, Mr. Harris was a Portfolio Manager at Fidelity Management &amp; Research Company (FMR Co.), the investment advisor for Fidelity’s family of mutual funds. Before joining Fidelity, Mr. Harris served as a Research Project Manager at Cambridge Associates, Inc. In this capacity, Mr. Harris researched, authored and managed dozens of investment publications, including “High-Yield Bonds” and “Putable Bond Strategies”, which formed a basis for asset allocation decisions for over 150 endowed institutions. He has been in the investment industry since 1989. He is a a CFA charterholder.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/Minicus_Digital.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Bob Minicus</h2>
                            <h3 class="title">President and Chief Executive Officer</h3>
                            <p>Bob Minicus is the President and Chief Executive Officer at Geode. Mr. Minicus is responsible for the overall management of Geode, including development of the firm’s long-term strategic planning and execution. Mr. Minicus joined Geode in 2021. He holds a B.A. in Economics from Amherst College.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/1-geode-phillip-bullen-heaadshot.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Philip Bullen, CFA</h2>
                            <h3 class="title"></h3>
                            <p>Phillip Bullen has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2017. Mr. Bullen has over 40 years of experience in the asset management industry as both a President/CEO and Chief Investment Officer. He has a broad investment experience across multiple asset classes including alternative investments. Mr. Bullen is a director of USA Pickleball. He was previously a member of the Deans Advisory Board at the Boston University School of Education, been a Trustee of Boston University, chair of the BU Investment Committee, a trustee and member of the investment committee at the Massachusetts Eye &amp; Ear Infirmary, a director of Aviva US, an advisor to the Man Group PLC, and a director of the Boston Society of Security Analysts. He is a CFA charterholder and a member of the South Florida Society of Security Analysts.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/2-geode-michael-even-heaadshot.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Michael Even, CFA</h2>
                            <h3 class="title"></h3>
                            <p>Michael Even has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2020. Mr. Even currently serves as: a Director of Investment Research and Strategy for FaithInvest; an Investment Committee member for Whitehead Institute; an Advisor for CircleUp; an Advisory Committee Member for KingsCrowd; an Advisory Board Member for Lumint Corporation; a Director and member of the Investment Committee for Osmosis Investment Management; an Advisor for Forge.AI; and a member of the Investment Committee of the Massachusetts Pension Reserves Management Board. Previously, he served as the Chairman and CEO of Man Numeric. Prior to Man Numeric, Mr. Even worked at Citigroup for nine years overseeing investment teams running nearly $500B in client assets. Prior to joining Citigroup, Mr. Even spent 13 years at Independence Investment Associates in Boston.  He is a a CFA charterholder.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/4-geode-kim-kenly-heaadshot.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Kim Kenly</h2>
                            <h3 class="title"></h3>
                            <p>Kim Kenly has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2012. Mr. Kenly currently serves as an Advisory Board Member for Rosemont Investment Partners, LLC and as a Senior Advisor for Lexington Wealth Management. He previously served as Managing Director of North American Sales and Marketing for Grantham, Mayo, Van Otterloo, LLC (GMO). Prior to GMO, he served as Managing Director of U.S. Sales and Marketing for Credit Suisse First Boston Investment Management Group. He also served as a Director for PanAgora Asset Management. He led the development and launch of the Structured Investment Products Group (the predecessor of PanAgora) within The Boston Company. He also served as the President, Board of Trustees, for the Cardigan Mountain School in Canaan, NH, where he is currently a Trustee.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/5-geode-arlene-rockefeller-headshot.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Arlene Rockefeller, CFA</h2>
                            <h3 class="title"></h3>
                            <p>Arlene Rockefeller has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2011. Ms. Rockefeller is on the Board of Advisors for Valsresso, LLC, a fintech company. Ms. Rockefeller was a partner at TruColor Capital Management, LLC from 2011 to 2013. Ms. Rockefeller previously worked at State Street Global Advisors in various management and portfolio management positions for 28 years. She most recently served as Global Equities CIO where she was responsible for active quantitative equities teams located in seven countries. Prior to her role as Global Equities CIO, Ms. Rockefeller served as the Head of Global Equities where she managed active and passive equity teams. She previously served as Head of Enhanced where she focused on the retention of assets and growth.  Ms. Rockefeller has over 40 years of investment industry experience. She is a a CFA charterholder.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/6-geode-eric-roiter-headshot.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Eric D. Roiter</h2>
                            <h3 class="title"></h3>
                            <p>Eric Roiter has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2013. Mr. Roiter previously was a Lecturer in Law at Boston University School of Law. In addition, from 1997 to June 2008, he served as Senior VP and General Counsel of Fidelity Management &amp; Research Company. In this role, Mr. Roiter was responsible for supervising and providing legal advice and representation for all aspects of Fidelity’s mutual fund business. From 1985 to 1997, Mr. Roiter was a corporate partner with Debevoise &amp; Plimpton, specializing in securities and financial services law. Previously, Mr. Roiter was with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission in Washington, D.C., serving in various legal positions, including Assistant General Counsel from 1979 to 1981.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/7-geode-jennifer-uhrig-heaadshot.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Jennifer Stonestreet Uhrig</h2>
                            <h3 class="title"></h3>
                            <p>Jennifer Uhrig has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2013. Ms. Uhrig is currently a Senior Equity Advisor for Fidelity Management &amp; Research Company, where she oversees Fine Structure Ventures, a venture capital fund investing in disruptive science. She also serves on the Board of Directors of COLT Group where she chairs the Audit committee and on the Board of Directors of eMoney Advisor and Hedron.Space. Previously, Ms. Uhrig worked in various roles at Fidelity as an equity analyst and fund manager for 22 years. In her diversified portfolio manager assignments, Ms. Uhrig managed start-up products as well as assets of up to $38 billion and consistently outperformed the benchmark on all of her funds. She joined Fidelity in 1987 as a research analyst covering the telecommunications industry. Prior to joining Fidelity, Ms. Uhrig was a research associate for Fred Alger Management from 1983 to 1985.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/8-geode-tom-sprague-heaadshot.jpg" width="1250" height="1250" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Thomas M. Sprague</h2>
                            <h3 class="title"></h3>
                            <p>Thomas Sprague has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2019. Mr. Sprague is a retired investment professional who remains an avid follower of markets and is active in providing financial and investment advice to several organizations in addition to actively managing his personal assets. He enjoys travel, fishing, golf, and wine collecting. He and his wife have two adult daughters.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
                    <div class="person">

                        <div class="headshot"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.geodecapital.com/sites/default/files/Alok%20Kapoor.jpg" width="402" height="402" alt="" /></div>
                        <div class="desc">
                            <h2>Alok Kapoor</h2>
                            <h3 class="title"></h3>
                            <p>Alok Kapoor has been a Director at Geode Capital Management since 2022. He was previously with Fidelity Investments from 2009 through 2019, most recently serving as Head of Advanced Process Solutions. Mr. Kapoor has over 30 years of experience in infrastructure technology, including roles as Executive Vice President of Enterprise Infrastructure and Chief Technology Officer. Since 1989, Mr. Kapoor has held various technology and infrastructure roles at Fidelity, Merrill Lynch, Harris Corporation and Trade.com. He has broad experience in delivery and execution across vast technology infrastructure portfolios including data centers, mainframes and market data. Mr. Kapoor is a Board Member for Boston Partners in Education and serves as a Trustee at his fraternity’s national foundation, The Kappa Delta Rho Foundation. His current focus is on targeted investing, philanthropy, and his family.</p>

                        </div>    </div>
